<h2>Premium LG Service in Bel Air</h2>
<p>Bel Air runs LG's flagship lineup. The diagnostic and service requirements for these machines differ from standard DLGX and DLE service:</p>

<p><strong>LG Signature DLEX9500V — steam system.</strong> Steam generator, water inlet valve, and steam nozzle in addition to standard heating components. When a DLEX9500V on Stone Canyon Road presents a CE or steam-specific error code, the first thing we do is distinguish between a steam system fault and a control board communication fault — they produce similar codes but require completely different fixes. Steam system fault: we check the water inlet valve for mineral buildup, test the steam generator heating element, and verify the steam nozzle isn't blocked. Control board fault: we run ThinQ diagnostics and check for WiFi interference before touching any hardware. Getting this distinction right on the first visit means one trip, not two. Steam system service follows LG's service documentation — we don't improvise on Signature machines.</p>

<p><strong>ThinQ diagnostics on AI DD models.</strong> The AI Direct Drive models common in Bel Air have the most sophisticated ThinQ diagnostic capability in the LG lineup. Error codes logged in the ThinQ app give us significant diagnostic information before we arrive. Share the ThinQ error code when you call — we frequently arrive with the specific part already identified and on the truck. This shortens the service visit by 20–30 minutes.</p>

<p><strong>Control board and WiFi interference.</strong> DLEX smart models occasionally develop control board errors when WiFi connectivity conflicts with ThinQ communication cycles — more common in tech-forward homes with complex smart home systems. Symptom: dryer starts normally, stops mid-cycle, shows CE or LE code with no mechanical cause. We run full ThinQ diagnostics before recommending any hardware replacement. Often a network configuration adjustment resolves the issue without parts. If the control board has failed from repeated error cycling: replacement $250–380.</p>

<p><strong>Drum bearing replacement on LG Signature.</strong> Low-frequency rumble developing gradually over months — the bearing failure signature. Sometimes first noticed by household staff. By the time we're called, the rumble is established but the machine still runs. Drum bearing plus rollers replaced together — same disassembly, rollers near end of life on any bearing-failure machine. Total: $320–400. Machine runs another 10+ years.</p>

